Ok well I had put this project to rest for a LONG time, and then I worked on it for a few more hours. I still haven't implemented the IRC protocol as it was suggested, but that will probably be the next step. 

Hopefully you guys can see a LITTLE bit of improvement. I posted this on mpsc, but as hardly anyone there is qualified to CC anything made in Java, I decided to post it here now too. I would like ways to make it better (besides implementing the IRC protocol, as it was already mentioned) so post any CC you can think of. 

Current Features:

    * Connect
    * Chatting
    * Simple GUI
    * Nick Changing
    * Color Coding
    * User List + Updating
    * Ban
    * Warn (Progressive, two warnings, then incremental mute times)
    * 5 lines, 5 seconds timer; if you go past it calls the warn method (see above) (pretty much the same as the IRC lines per second feature)
    * Nick Registration & Login
    * Private Messaging (pretty crappy atm; I plan to either tab it [when I implement the IRC protocol] or have a new 'PM window')
    * Kick
    * Promote/Demote

And yes, I know the colors are gay.
